{
  "texts": [
    "Specifically, the hidden state of RNN in the current time step is related to not only the current input but also the hidden state in the former time step.",
    "This recurrent connection mechanism enables the RNN to learn the pattern of sequential data.",
    "In addition, the basic architecture of RNN is illustrated in Figure 8, where X t, S t, and Y t refer to the input layer, hidden layer, and output layer in the tth time step, respectively.",
    "U, V, and W are the learnable parameters.",
    "The output of RNN in the tth time slot can be formulated asS t+1 = f (W S t + U X t+1), (13a) Y t+1 = V S t+1,(13b)where f (•) represents the activation function."
  ]
}